-- Alcoa sells packaging unit for $2.7 billion
-- 
-- Fri Dec 21, 2007 6:41pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/21/businesspro-alcoa-deal-dc-idUSWEN315220071221

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Alcoa ( AA.N ) on Friday said it has 
agreed to sell its packaging and consumer businesses to New 
Zealand's Rank Group Limited for $2.7 billion in cash. 

  The transaction is expected to be completed by the end of 
the first quarter 2008, the company said.  (Reporting by  Michael Flaherty )